div.p:
Xpath is a standard syntax for matching parts of an XML tree in terms of its
                    elements and attributes 

//p : any p anywhere

//p[anchor] : any p containing an
                                anchor

//p[@rend]  : any p with a rend
                            attribute

//p[starts-with(@rend,'Head')] any p whose
                                rend attribute has a value starting with
                            Head
